        "content": "<p>If I write <code>have x := t</code>, can I get a proof of <code>x = t</code> somehow? Or do I need to do something else for that?</p>",
        "id": 206962901,
        "sender_full_name": "Andre Knispel",
        "timestamp": 1597430453
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><code>have</code> hides this, but <code>let</code> (same syntax) doesn't.</p>",
        "id": 206962979,
        "sender_full_name": "Heather Macbeth",
        "timestamp": 1597430519
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>even better, <code>set x := t with hxt</code> will give you a name for the proof. With <code>let</code> the equality is definitional but doesn't have a name.</p>",
        "id": 206963416,
        "sender_full_name": "Kevin Buzzard",
        "timestamp": 1597430766
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Ah, <code>set</code> is perfect!</p>",
